'''Cross-laminates''' are synthetic, flexible [[film]]s of which the properties have been enhanced via mechanical [[wikt:manipulate|manipulation]] of the film. Nowadays, the most well-known type of cross-laminated films are the [[Valéron]] films.

[[Category:Materials]]


{{material-stub}}

'''Hugh Auchincloss Brown''' (23 December 1879 – 19 November 1975) was an electrical engineer best known for advancing a [[pole shift theory|theory of catastrophic pole shift]].  Brown claimed that massive accumulation of ice at the [[geographical pole|poles]] caused recurring tipping of the [[axis of rotation|axis]] in cycles of approximately 4000–7500 years.  Brown argued that because the earth wobbles on the axis and the crust slides on the mantle, a shift was demonstrably imminent, and suggested the use of [[nuclear explosion]]s to break up the ice to forestall catastrophe.

==Works==
* ''Popular awakening concerning the impending flood'' (privately printed 1948)
* [http://www.habtheory.com/3/index.php ''Cataclysms of the Earth''] (1967)

